Package com.jscape.inet.dns.record

Class Summary
Address Address record represents a host address.
CanonicalName CanonicalName record specifies the canonical or primary name for the owner of a domain name.
DnsRecord Represents a resource record retrieved from a Dns server.
HostInfo HostInfo records are used to acquire general information about a host.
MailBox MailBox represents a mailbox domain name.
MailDomain MailDomain record represents a mail-destination.
MailExchanger MailExchanger record represents a host responsible for sending email
MailExchangerComparator Implements methods for sorting MailExchanger records by preference.
MailForwarder MailForwarder record represents a mail forwarder domain.
MailGroup MailGroup record represents a mail group member.
MailInfo MailInfo record represents a mailbox or mail list information.
MailRename MailRename record represents a mail rename domain name.
NameServer NameServer record represents an authoritative nameserver.
Null Null record may contain any data.
Pointer Pointer record is used in special domains to point to some other location in the domain space
StartOfAuthority StartOfAuthority record marks the start of a zone of authority.
Text Text record is used to hold descriptive text.
WellKnownServices WellKnownServices record is used to describe the well known services supported by a particular protocol on a particular internet address.
